    <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
    <p>
      Roku TV does not require users to create an account and does not directly
      collect personal information such as name, email address, phone number, or
      payment information.
    </p>
    <p>
      However, some information may be collected automatically through third-party
      services used inside the app, including advertising services.
    </p>

    <h2>2. Information Collected Automatically</h2>
    <p>
      When you use the app, certain technical information may be collected
      automatically, such as:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Device type and model</li>
      <li>Operating system version</li>
      <li>App usage information</li>
      <li>Advertising identifiers</li>
      <li>Approximate location information</li>
      <li>Crash logs and performance data</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      This information may be used to improve app performance, show ads, prevent
      fraud, and understand how users interact with the app.
    </p>

    <h2>3. Third-Party Advertising</h2>
    <p>
      Roku TV uses third-party advertising services to display ads in the app.
      These services may collect and use certain information to provide,
      personalize, and measure ads.
    </p>

    <h2>4. AppLovin</h2>
    <p>
      Roku TV uses AppLovin advertising services. AppLovin may collect and use
      information from your device for advertising, analytics, fraud prevention,
      and related purposes.
    </p>
    <p>
      For more information about AppLovin’s collection and use of your information,
      please visit:
      <a href="https://legal.applovin.com/privacy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
        https://legal.applovin.com/privacy/
      </a>
    </p>

    <h2>5. How We Use Information</h2>
    <p>
      Information collected through the app or third-party services may be used to:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Provide and improve the app experience</li>
      <li>Display advertisements</li>
      <li>Measure ad performance</li>
      <li>Analyze app usage and performance</li>
      <li>Detect, prevent, and address technical issues or fraud</li>
      <li>Comply with legal obligations</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>6. Movie Information</h2>
    <p>
      Roku TV may display movie-related information such as titles, posters,
      ratings, genres, release dates, descriptions, and recommendations. This
      information is used only to help users discover and organize movies.
    </p>
    <p>
      Roku TV does not host, stream, sell, or distribute movies or video content.
    </p>

    <h2>7. Cookies and Similar Technologies</h2>
    <p>
      The app itself may not use browser cookies. However, third-party services,
      including advertising providers, may use similar technologies such as
      device identifiers, SDKs, and tracking technologies to provide and measure
      ads.
    </p>

    <h2>8. Children’s Privacy</h2>
    <p>
      Roku TV is not intended for children under the age of 13. We do not
      knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If you
      believe that a child has provided us with personal information, please
      contact us so we can take appropriate action.
    </p>

    <h2>9. Data Sharing</h2>
    <p>
      We do not sell personal information directly. However, third-party
      advertising services may collect and process data according to their own
      privacy policies. Information may be shared with service providers that help
      operate, improve, analyze, or monetize the app.
    </p>

    <h2>10. Your Privacy Choices</h2>
    <p>
      Depending on your device and location, you may have privacy choices such as:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Resetting your advertising ID from your device settings</li>
      <li>Limiting ad personalization from your device settings</li>
      <li>Managing consent choices where available</li>
      <li>Requesting information or deletion where applicable by law</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>11. Data Security</h2>
    <p>
      We take reasonable steps to protect information associated with the app.
      However, no method of electronic transmission or storage is completely
      secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.
    </p>

    <h2>12. Links to Third-Party Services</h2>
    <p>
      The app may contain links or references to third-party services. We are not
      responsible for the privacy practices, content, or policies of third-party
      websites or services.
    </p>

    <h2>13. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
    <p>
      We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be
      posted on this page with an updated “Last updated” date. Your continued use
      of the app after changes are posted means you accept the updated policy.
    </p>

